Function to convert the images into 1-D vector or Dataframe.¶

In [9]:
def get_data(df,path,types=None):
    
    #path='/kaggle/input/data-centric-ai-competition-2023-image-data/train'
    img_vec=[]
    for file in df['img']:
        # Load image as grayscale
        img = Image.open(os.path.join(path, file)).convert('L')
        img=img.resize((28,28))

        # Convert image to numpy array

        img_array = np.array(img, dtype=np.float32) / 255.0

        # Flatten array to 1D
        img_1d = img_array.flatten()
        img_vec.append(img_1d)
    if types=='df':
        x=pd.DataFrame(img_vec)
        
    else:
        x=pd.DataFrame(img_vec)
        x=x.to_numpy()
        x= x.reshape(len(x), 1, 28, 28)  
    return x

Create pytorch sequential model to classify the image¶

In [10]:
class ClassifierModule(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self):
        super().__init__()

        self.cnn = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(1, 6, 3),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(6),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2),
            nn.Conv2d(6, 16, 3),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(16),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2),
        )
        self.out = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Flatten(),
            nn.LazyLinear(128),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Linear(128, 33),
            nn.Softmax(dim=-1),
        )

    def forward(self, X):
        X = self.cnn(X)
        X = self.out(X)
        return X

Create the class to find the incorrect label images.¶

In [13]:
class Label_issue_finder():
    def __init__(self,df,path):
        self.df=df
        self.path=path
        self.misslabled_images=list()  
        
    def get_data(self):
        x=get_data(self.df,self.path)
        return x
    
    
    def model(self):
        model_skorch = NeuralNetClassifier(ClassifierModule, max_epochs=50,verbose=0,
                                          device = 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')
        kf=KFold(n_splits=10, random_state=45, shuffle=True)
        for i in range(4):#4 good result
            x=self.get_data()
            pred_probs = cross_val_predict(model_skorch,x, self.df['label'].values,
                               cv=kf,
                               method='predict_proba',verbose=50)
            predicted_labels = pred_probs.argmax(axis=1)
            acc = accuracy_score(self.df['label'].values, predicted_labels)

            print(f"Cross-validated estimate of accuracy on held-out data: {acc}")
            ranked_label_issues = find_label_issues(self.df['label'].values, pred_probs, return_indices_ranked_by="self_confidence")
            self.misslabled_images.extend(self.df[self.df.index.isin(ranked_label_issues)]['img'].values)
            print(f"Iteration: {i}, Number of Misslabled Images: {len(ranked_label_issues)}")
            self.df=self.df.drop(ranked_label_issues)
            self.df=self.df.reset_index(drop=True)
        print(f"Total Number of Misslabled Images: {len(self.misslabled_images)}")

def img_read(path,im ,new_size=False):
    img = Image.open(f"{(os.path.join(path, im))}")
    #img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    if new_size:
        img=img.resize((224,224))
        return img
    else:
        return img

Create a class to show different evaluation metric plot.¶

In [34]:
class Eval_metric_plot():
    def __init__(self,y_true,y_pred,y_pred_prob=None):
        self.y_true=y_true
        self.y_pred=y_pred
        self.y_pred_prob=y_pred_prob
        self.num_class=len(set(self.y_true))
    
    def plot_df(self,score_list,name):
        df=pd.DataFrame({'class':[*range(self.num_class)],f'{name}':score_list})
        df['class']=lbl.inverse_transform(df[['class']])
        df['class_type']=df['class'].apply(lambda x:"Numbers" if len(re.findall("\d+",x))>0 else "Letters")
        df=df.sort_values(f'{name}',ascending=False)
        return df
    
    def result_plot(self,df,title=None):
        palette = sns.color_palette(cc.glasbey, n_colors=26)
        sns.set_style("whitegrid")
        g=sns.catplot(data=df,hue='class',
        y='class',x=df.columns[1]  ,col='class_type',kind='point',sharex=False,sharey=False,legend=False,palette=palette);
        g.fig.suptitle(f"{title}",size=18)
        plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.9)
        for ax in g.axes.flat:
                ax.xaxis.grid(False)
                ax.yaxis.grid(True)
       
    
    def true_positive_plot(self,plot=True):
        conf_mat = confusion_matrix(self.y_true, self.y_pred)
        n_classes = conf_mat.shape[0]
        tpr_scores = []
        for i in range(n_classes):
            tp = conf_mat[i, i]
            fn = np.sum(conf_mat[i, :]) - tp
            tpr = tp / (tp + fn)
            tpr_scores.append(tpr)
        if plot :
            self.result_plot(self.plot_df(tpr_scores,name="True_Positive_Rate"),title="True Positive Rate")
        else:
            return self.plot_df(tpr_scores,name="True_Positive_Rate")
    
    def true_negative_plot(self,plot=True):
        conf_mat = confusion_matrix(self.y_true, self.y_pred)
        n_classes = conf_mat.shape[0]
        tnr_scores = []
        for i in range(n_classes):
            tn = np.sum( np.delete(np.delete(conf_mat, i, axis=0), i, axis=1))
            tp = conf_mat[i, i]
            fp = np.sum(conf_mat[:, i]) - tp
            tnr = tn / (tn + fp)
            tnr_scores.append(tnr)
        if plot:
            self.result_plot(self.plot_df(tnr_scores,name="True_Negative_Rate"),title="True Negative Rate")
        else:
            return self.plot_df(tnr_scores,name="True_Negative_Rate")
            
    def false_positive_plot(self,plot=True):
        conf_mat = confusion_matrix(self.y_true, self.y_pred)
        n_classes = conf_mat.shape[0]
        fpr_scores = []
        for i in range(n_classes):
            tp = conf_mat[i, i]
            fp = np.sum(conf_mat[:, i]) - tp
            tn = np.sum( np.delete(np.delete(conf_mat, i, axis=0), i, axis=1))
            fpr = fp / (fp + tn)
            fpr_scores.append(fpr)
        if plot:
            self.result_plot(self.plot_df(fpr_scores,name="False_Positive_Rate"),title="False Positive Rate")
        else:
            return self.plot_df(fpr_scores,name="False_Positive_Rate")
        
    def false_negative_plot(self,plot=True):
        conf_mat = confusion_matrix(self.y_true, self.y_pred)
        n_classes = conf_mat.shape[0]
        fnr_scores = []
        for i in range(n_classes):
            tp = conf_mat[i, i]
            fn = np.sum(conf_mat[i, :]) - tp
            fnr = fn / (fn + tp)
            fnr_scores.append(fnr)
        if plot:
            self.result_plot(self.plot_df(fnr_scores,name="False_Negative_Rate"),title="False Negative Rate")
        else:
            return self.plot_df(fnr_scores,name="False_Negative_Rate")
    def false_discovery_plot(self,plot=True):
        conf_mat = confusion_matrix(self.y_true, self.y_pred)
        n_classes = conf_mat.shape[0]
        fdr_scores = []
        for i in range(n_classes):
            tp = conf_mat[i, i]
            fp = np.sum(conf_mat[:, i]) - tp
            fdr = fp / (fp + tp)
            fdr_scores.append(fdr)
        if plot:
            self.result_plot(self.plot_df(fdr_scores,name="False_Discovery_Rate"),title="False Discovery Rate")
        else:
            return self.plot_df(fdr_scores,name="False_Discovery_Rate")
        
    def false_omission_plot(self,plot=True):
        conf_mat = confusion_matrix(self.y_true, self.y_pred)
        n_classes = conf_mat.shape[0]
        for_scores = []
        for i in range(n_classes):
            tp = conf_mat[i, i]
            fn = np.sum(conf_mat[i, :]) - tp
            tn = np.sum( np.delete(np.delete(conf_mat, i, axis=0), i, axis=1))
            for_val = fn / (fn + tn)
            for_scores.append(for_val)
        if plot:
            self.result_plot(self.plot_df(for_scores,name="False_Omission_Rate"),title="False Omission Rate")
        else:
            return self.plot_df(for_scores,name="False_Omission_Rate")
    def roc_auc_score_plot(self,plot=True):
        binary_test = label_binarize(self.y_true,classes=[*range(self.num_class)])
        roc_auc_scores=[]
        for i in range(self.num_class):
            roc_auc_scores.append(roc_auc_score(binary_test[:,i], self.y_pred_prob[:,i],average='weighted',multi_class='ovo'))
        if plot:
            self.result_plot(self.plot_df(roc_auc_scores,name="ROC_AUC_Score"),title="ROC AUC Score")
        else:
            return self.plot_df(roc_auc_scores,name="ROC_AUC_Score")
    def confusion_matrix_plot(self,types='combine'):
        if types=='sep':
            fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(nrows=2, figsize=(15, 15))
            sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(self.y_true,self.y_pred)[:7,:7], annot=True,  cmap="inferno",ax=ax1);
            ax1.set_title("Confusion Matrix : Numbers")
            ax1.set_xlabel("Predicted Numbers")
            ax1.set_ylabel("Actual Numbers")
            ax1.xaxis.set_ticklabels(re.findall("(\d+)",str(lbl.classes_)))
            ax1.yaxis.set_ticklabels(re.findall("(\d+)",str(lbl.classes_)),rotation=0)
            sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(self.y_true,self.y_pred)[7:,7:], annot=True,  cmap="inferno",ax=ax2);
            ax2.set_title("Confusion Matrix : Letters")
            ax2.set_xlabel("Predicted Letters")
            ax2.set_ylabel("Actual Letters")
            ax2.xaxis.set_ticklabels(re.findall("([a-z]+)",str(lbl.classes_)))
            ax2.yaxis.set_ticklabels(re.findall("([a-z]+)",str(lbl.classes_)),rotation=0)
        elif types=='combine':
            fig, (ax1) = plt.subplots(nrows=1, figsize=(30, 20))
            sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(self.y_true,self.y_pred), annot=True,  cmap="inferno");
            ax1.set_title("Confusion Matrix : Numbers & Letters")
            ax1.set_xlabel("Predicted Numbers & Letters")
            ax1.set_ylabel("Actual Numbers & Letters")
            ax1.xaxis.set_ticklabels(lbl.classes_)
            ax1.yaxis.set_ticklabels(lbl.classes_,rotation=0)

Let's blend 3 shallow model and one deep model.¶

In [46]:
class blend_models():
    def __init__(self,train,test):
        self.train=train
        self.test=test
        self.test_transformed=0
        self.train_transformed=0
        self.X_train=0
        self.X_test=0
        self.y_train=0
        self.y_test=0
        self.validation_result=dict()
        self.test_result=dict()
        self.models=dict()
        
    @staticmethod
    def convert_array(df):
        x=pd.DataFrame(df)
        x=x.to_numpy()
        x= x.reshape(len(x), 1, 28, 28) 
        return x
   

    def plot_accuracy(self,model_name):
        self.model_name=model_name
        if model_name=='Nnet':
            result=classification_report(self.y_test,
                                                 self.models[self.model_name].predict(blend.convert_array(blend.X_test)),
                                                 output_dict=True,
                                                 digits=5)
        else:
            result=classification_report(self.y_test,
                                                 self.models[self.model_name].predict(self.X_test),
                                                 output_dict=True,
                                                 digits=5)    
        df=pd.DataFrame(columns=['class','f1_score'])
        for i in [ i  for i in result.keys() if i not in ['accuracy', 'macro avg', 'weighted avg']]:
            df.loc[len(df)]=[i,result[i]['f1-score']]

        df['class']=lbl.inverse_transform(df[['class']].astype('int'))
        df['class_type']=df['class'].apply(lambda x:"Numbers" if len(re.findall("\d+",x))>0 else "Letters")
        
        _=sns.catplot(data=df.sort_values('f1_score',ascending=False),hue='class_type',
            x='f1_score',y='class',col='class_type',kind='bar',sharex=False,sharey=False,).\
        fig.suptitle(f"{self.model_name} Model Score \n\n\n" ,fontsize=18);
        
    def precision_recall_curve(self,model_name):
        self.model_name=model_name
        precision = dict()
        recall = dict()
        for i in range(33):
            precision[i], recall[i], _ = precision_recall_curve(label_binarize(self.y_test,classes=[*range(33)])[:,i],
                                                                self.models[self.model_name].predict_proba(self.X_test)[:, i])
            plt.plot(recall[i], precision[i], lw=2, label=f'class {lbl.inverse_transform([[i]])}')

        plt.xlabel("recall")
        plt.ylabel("precision")
        plt.legend(loc="best")
        plt.title("precision vs. recall curve")
        plt.show()
       

        
    
       
    
    
    
        
        
    def blend(self):
        self.train_transformed=get_data(self.train,"/kaggle/input/data-centric-ai-competition-2023-image-data/train",types='df')
        self.test_transformed=get_data(self.test,"/kaggle/input/data-centric-ai-competition-2023-image-data/val",types='df')
        self.X_train, self.X_test, self.y_train, self.y_test = train_test_split(
                                         self.train_transformed, self.train['label'].values, 
                                            test_size=0.33, 
                                random_state=42,stratify= self.train['label'].values)
        models=[('KNN',KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=1)),
                #("lightgbm",LGBMClassifier(random_state=48,verbose=-1)),
               # ("xgboost",XGBClassifier(verbosity=0)),
                ("Random_forest",RandomForestClassifier(random_state=48)),
                ("Extratree",ExtraTreesClassifier(random_state=48)),
                ("Nnet",NeuralNetClassifier(ClassifierModule, max_epochs=50,verbose=0,
                                                           device = 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'))]
        for model_name ,model in models:
            if model_name=='Nnet':
                model.fit(blend_models.convert_array(self.X_train),self.y_train)
                val_pre_df=model.predict(blend_models.convert_array(self.X_test))
                score=accuracy_score(self.y_test,model.predict(blend_models.convert_array(self.X_test)))
                test_pre_df=model.predict(blend_models.convert_array(self.test_transformed))
                self.models[f"{model_name}"]=model
                print("-"*100)
                print(f"{model_name} accuracy_score: {score} ")
                print("-"*100)
                self.validation_result[f"validation_{model_name}"]=val_pre_df
                self.test_result[f"test_{model_name}"]=test_pre_df
                                     
            else:
                model.fit(self.X_train,self.y_train)
                val_pre_df=model.predict(self.X_test)
                score=accuracy_score(self.y_test,model.predict(self.X_test))
                test_pre_df=model.predict(self.test_transformed)
                self.models[f"{model_name}"]=model
                print("-"*100)
                print(f"{model_name} accuracy_score: {score} ")
                print("-"*100)
                self.validation_result[f"validation_{model_name}"]=val_pre_df
                self.test_result[f"test_{model_name}"]=test_pre_df
